@article.set_title "How to respond to UK companies that are ‘Right for opportunity"



@article.set_section "Overview", <<-SECTION_1

<p>This guidance is for staff and partners overseas. Use the guidance to help you reply to a UK company that is right for the opportunity it has submitted a proposal for.</p>
<h2>‘Right for opportunity’ explained</h2>
<p>A company is deemed to be ‘Right for opportunity’ if it:</p>
<ul>
  <li>is eligible</li>
  <li>meets the criteria of the buyer or tender</li>
  <li>has the logistical and financial capacity to deliver</li>
</ul>

SECTION_1



@article.set_section "What you need to do", <<-SECTION_2

<p>Tell the UK company what the next step is. This will be one of the following:</p>
<a href="#">The company details will be forwarded on to the buyer</a><br />
<a href="#">The company and buyer will be introduced to each other</a><br />
<a href="#">The company will need to contact the buyer directly</a><br />
<a href="#">The company will be given more information about a tender</a><br />
<p>Each step has a list of suggested sentences to help you write your response. If applicable, UK companies will be informed of UK export finance and the relevant country guide and DIT regional office within our internal system so do not include this information.</p>

SECTION_2



@article.set_section "Forward company details on to the buyer", <<-SECTION_3

<p>Include in your response:</p>
<ul>
  <li>who the buyer is</li>
  <li>further details about the opportunity</li>
  <li>what happens next and what the company needs to do</li>
  <li>a request for more information such as marketing materials (if applicable)</li>
  <li>relevant documents (if applicable)</li>
</ul>

<p>Use sentences such as:</p>
<ul class="examples">
  <li class="good">The buyer is <span>{buyer’s name, description and website}</span></li>
  <li class="good">I will forward your details on to the buyer. They will contact you directly if they are interested in working with you.</li>  
  <li class="good">I will forward your details onto the buyer, they will let me know if they are interested in working with you.</li>
  <li class="good">The buyer may take a few weeks to respond or sometimes may not respond at all. Buyer priorities change all the time. We have no say in their decisions or how they work.</li>
  <li class="good">The buyer would like to know if your company can <span>{ask a question}</span></li>
  <li class="good">My role in managing this opportunity has now come to an end.</li>
  <li class="good">You can copy me into your correspondence with the buyer. I’ll do my best to help you along the way.</li></ul>

